Package: dockeRviz
Type: Package
Title: Visualize Dockerfiles in R
Version: 1.0.2
Author: Matt Majestic
Maintainer: Matt Majestic <mattmajestic@strictlyresearch.com>
Description: Provides tools to visualize Docker and Docker Compose in R. 
    It allows users to analyze and understand the structure and steps involved in Docker configurations
    through graphical representations. This can be particularly useful for professionals
    and developers working with Docker to quickly get insights into their Docker configurations.
License: MIT
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.6)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
Imports:
    fastmap,
    plotly,
    RColorBrewer,
    htmltools,
    yaml,
    magrittr,
    tibble,
    DT,
    shiny,
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
